message.content: Case report of a 62-year-old male with relapsed/refractory multiple myeloma who achieved a partial response with daratumumab and pomalidomide.
Case report of a 65-year-old male with relapsed refractory multiple myeloma treated with daratumumab and pomalidomide.
A 65-year-old male with multiple myeloma and a history of hypertension, hyperlipidemia, and diabetes mellitus was successfully treated with lenalidomide and dexamethasone.

A 67-year-old male with relapsed refractory multiple myeloma achieved a partial response with a combination of pomalidomide and dexamethasone. 

A 52-year-old female with multiple myeloma and severe renal impairment achieved a durable response with a combination of carfilzomib, lenalidomide, and dexamethasone.
